An iconic 50-year-old elephant bull was killed in Namibia by a hunter. The elephant, popularly known as "Voortrekker", was killed in the Omatjete area, and was part of the rare Ugab desert-adapted herd. Although he was authorised by the government to do so, the elephant's death caused an uproar. Baby elephant takes first wobbly steps The Asian elephant was born at Pairi Daiza zoo in Belgium.